            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EDavid%20insisted%20on%20paying%20the%20full%20price%20for%20Araunah's%20threshing%20floor.%20The%20idea%20of%20making%20an%20offering%20to%20God%20with%20no%20personal%20sacrifice%20involved%20repulsed%20David.%20His%20God%20was%20entirely%20too%20holy%20and%20worthy%20to%20be%20offered%20a%20cheap%20sacrifice.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EMany%20Christians%20are%20looking%20for%20the%20%22bargain%20table%2C%22%20where%20they%20can%20serve%20the%20Lord%20with%20little%20or%20no%20personal%20change%20in%20their%20lifestyles%20or%20comfort%20levels.%20The%20Bible%20tells%20of%20many%20such%20people%2C%20who%20desired%20the%20environment%20of%20religion%20without%20the%20demonstration%20of%20true%20love%20for%20God%20or%20man.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAll%20love%20is%20shown%20by%20personal%20sacrifice.%20Jesus%20vividly%20portrayed%20His%20love%20for%20us%20by%20paying%20the%20full%20price%20for%20our%20sin.%20He%20took%20no%20shortcuts%20or%20easy%20roads%20to%20purchase%20our%20redemption.%20Willingly%2C%20He%20drank%20the%20full%20cup%20of%20God's%20wrath.%20He's%20asking%20us%20today%2C%20%22Have%20you%20resigned%20everything%20to%20Me%20and%20counted%20it%20as%20loss%20that%20you%20might%20gain%20Me%3F%20Are%20you%20willing%20to%20pay%20the%20full%20price%3F%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20takes%20seemingly%20insignificant%20sacrifices%20and%20uses%20them%20to%20build%20His%20mighty%20kingdom.%20David%20had%20no%20idea%20that%20his%20little%20seed%20of%20sacrifice%20at%20the%20threshing%20floor%20of%20Araunah%20would%20ultimately%20lead%20to%20the%20establishment%20of%20Solomon's%20temple%20at%20that%20very%20site%20(2%20Chronicles%203%3A1).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhat%20have%20you%20offered%20to%20the%20Lord%20in%20loving%20sacrifice%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Chronicles.19:1-21:30",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Chronicles%2019%3A1-21%3A30%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Defeats%20the%20Ammonites%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESome%20time%20after%20this%2C%20King%20Nahash%20of%20the%20Ammonites%20died%2C%20and%20his%20son%20Hanun%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BSam%2010%3A1%3B%20Hebrew%20lacks%20%3Cem%3EHanun.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20became%20king.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20going%20to%20show%20loyalty%20to%20Hanun%20because%20his%20father%2C%20Nahash%2C%20was%20always%20loyal%20to%20me.%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20David%20sent%20messengers%20to%20express%20sympathy%20to%20Hanun%20about%20his%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20death.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EBut%20when%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20ambassadors%20arrived%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Ammon%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3Ethe%20Ammonite%20commanders%20said%20to%20Hanun%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BDo%20you%20really%20think%20these%20men%20are%20coming%20here%20to%20honor%20your%20father%3F%20No!%20David%20has%20sent%20them%20to%20spy%20out%20the%20land%20so%20they%20can%20come%20in%20and%20conquer%20it!%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Hanun%20seized%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20ambassadors%20and%20shaved%20them%2C%20cut%20off%20their%20robes%20at%20the%20buttocks%2C%20and%20sent%20them%20back%20to%20David%20in%20shame.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20David%20heard%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20the%20men%2C%20he%20sent%20messengers%20to%20tell%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BStay%20at%20Jericho%20until%20your%20beards%20grow%20out%2C%20and%20then%20come%20back.%26%23x201D%3B%20For%20they%20felt%20deep%20shame%20because%20of%20their%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20people%20of%20Ammon%20realized%20how%20seriously%20they%20had%20angered%20David%2C%20Hanun%20and%20the%20Ammonites%20sent%2075%2C000%20pounds%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E1%2C000%20talents%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B34%2C000%20kilograms%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20silver%20to%20hire%20chariots%20and%20charioteers%20from%20Aram-naharaim%2C%20Aram-maacah%2C%20and%20Zobah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20also%20hired%2032%2C000%20chariots%20and%20secured%20the%20support%20of%20the%20king%20of%20Maacah%20and%20his%20army.%20These%20forces%20camped%20at%20Medeba%2C%20where%20they%20were%20joined%20by%20the%20Ammonite%20troops%20that%20Hanun%20had%20recruited%20from%20his%20own%20towns.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20David%20heard%20about%20this%2C%20he%20sent%20Joab%20and%20all%20his%20warriors%20to%20fight%20them.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Ammonite%20troops%20came%20out%20and%20drew%20up%20their%20battle%20lines%20at%20the%20entrance%20of%20the%20city%2C%20while%20the%20other%20kings%20positioned%20themselves%20to%20fight%20in%20the%20open%20fields.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Joab%20saw%20that%20he%20would%20have%20to%20fight%20on%20both%20the%20front%20and%20the%20rear%2C%20he%20chose%20some%20of%20Israel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20elite%20troops%20and%20placed%20them%20under%20his%20personal%20command%20to%20fight%20the%20Arameans%20in%20the%20fields.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20left%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20army%20under%20the%20command%20of%20his%20brother%20Abishai%2C%20who%20was%20to%20attack%20the%20Ammonites.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BIf%20the%20Arameans%20are%20too%20strong%20for%20me%2C%20then%20come%20over%20and%20help%20me%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Joab%20told%20his%20brother.%20%26%23x201C%3BAnd%20if%20the%20Ammonites%20are%20too%20strong%20for%20you%2C%20I%20will%20help%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EBe%20courageous!%20Let%20us%20fight%20bravely%20for%20our%20people%20and%20the%20cities%20of%20our%20God.%20May%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20will%20be%20done.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Joab%20and%20his%20troops%20attacked%2C%20the%20Arameans%20began%20to%20run%20away.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20when%20the%20Ammonites%20saw%20the%20Arameans%20running%2C%20they%20also%20ran%20from%20Abishai%20and%20retreated%20into%20the%20city.%20Then%20Joab%20returned%20to%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Arameans%20now%20realized%20that%20they%20were%20no%20match%20for%20Israel%2C%20so%20they%20sent%20messengers%20and%20summoned%20additional%20Aramean%20troops%20from%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20Euphrates%20River.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A16a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20river.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20These%20troops%20were%20under%20the%20command%20of%20Shobach%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A16b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BSam%2010%3A16%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EShophach%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2019%3A18.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20commander%20of%20Hadadezer%26%23x2019%3Bs%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20David%20heard%20what%20was%20happening%2C%20he%20mobilized%20all%20Israel%2C%20crossed%20the%20Jordan%20River%2C%20and%20positioned%20his%20troops%20in%20battle%20formation.%20Then%20David%20engaged%20the%20Arameans%20in%20battle%2C%20and%20they%20fought%20against%20him.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20again%20the%20Arameans%20fled%20from%20the%20Israelites.%20This%20time%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20forces%20killed%207%2C000%20charioteers%20and%2040%2C000%20foot%20soldiers%2C%20including%20Shobach%2C%20the%20commander%20of%20their%20army.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_19_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Hadadezer%26%23x2019%3Bs%20allies%20saw%20that%20they%20had%20been%20defeated%20by%20Israel%2C%20they%20surrendered%20to%20David%20and%20became%20his%20subjects.%20After%20that%2C%20the%20Arameans%20were%20no%20longer%20willing%20to%20help%20the%20Ammonites.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Captures%20Rabbah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20spring%20of%20the%20year%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EAt%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20first%20day%20of%20the%20year%20in%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20occurred%20in%20March%20or%20April.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20when%20kings%20normally%20go%20out%20to%20war%2C%20Joab%20led%20the%20Israelite%20army%20in%20successful%20attacks%20against%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Ammonites.%20In%20the%20process%20he%20laid%20siege%20to%20the%20city%20of%20Rabbah%2C%20attacking%20and%20destroying%20it.%20However%2C%20David%20stayed%20behind%20in%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20David%20went%20to%20Rabbah%20and%20removed%20the%20crown%20from%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20head%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A2a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Efrom%20the%20head%20of%20Milcom%3C%2Fem%3E%20(as%20in%20Greek%20version%20and%20Latin%20Vulgate).%20Milcom%2C%20also%20called%20Molech%2C%20was%20the%20god%20of%20the%20Ammonites.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20it%20was%20placed%20on%20his%20own%20head.%20The%20crown%20was%20made%20of%20gold%20and%20set%20with%20gems%2C%20and%20he%20found%20that%20it%20weighed%20seventy-five%20pounds.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A2b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E1%26%23xA0%3Btalent%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B34%26%23xA0%3Bkilograms%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20David%20took%20a%20vast%20amount%20of%20plunder%20from%20the%20city.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20also%20made%20slaves%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Rabbah%20and%20forced%20them%20to%20labor%20with%20saws%2C%20iron%20picks%2C%20and%20iron%20axes.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BSam%2012%3A31%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Eand%20cut%20them%20with%20saws%2C%20iron%20picks%2C%20and%20saws.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20That%20is%20how%20David%20dealt%20with%20the%20people%20of%20all%20the%20Ammonite%20towns.%20Then%20David%20and%20all%20the%20army%20returned%20to%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EBattles%20against%20Philistine%20Giants%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20this%2C%20war%20broke%20out%20with%20the%20Philistines%20at%20Gezer.%20As%20they%20fought%2C%20Sibbecai%20from%20Hushah%20killed%20Saph%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A4a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20text%20at%202%26%23xA0%3BSam%2021%3A18%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3ESippai.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20a%20descendant%20of%20the%20giants%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A4b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Edescendant%20of%20the%20Rephaites%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2020%3A6%2C%208.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20so%20the%20Philistines%20were%20subdued.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EDuring%20another%20battle%20with%20the%20Philistines%2C%20Elhanan%20son%20of%20Jair%20killed%20Lahmi%2C%20the%20brother%20of%20Goliath%20of%20Gath.%20The%20handle%20of%20Lahmi%26%23x2019%3Bs%20spear%20was%20as%20thick%20as%20a%20weaver%26%23x2019%3Bs%20beam!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20another%20battle%20with%20the%20Philistines%20at%20Gath%2C%20they%20encountered%20a%20huge%20man%20with%20six%20fingers%20on%20each%20hand%20and%20six%20toes%20on%20each%20foot%2C%20twenty-four%20in%20all%2C%20who%20was%20also%20a%20descendant%20of%20the%20giants.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20when%20he%20defied%20and%20taunted%20Israel%2C%20he%20was%20killed%20by%20Jonathan%2C%20the%20son%20of%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20brother%20Shimea.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_20_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20Philistines%20were%20descendants%20of%20the%20giants%20of%20Gath%2C%20but%20David%20and%20his%20warriors%20killed%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_21_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Takes%20a%20Census%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESatan%20rose%20up%20against%20Israel%20and%20caused%20David%20to%20take%20a%20census%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_21_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20said%20to%20Joab%20and%20the%20commanders%20of%20the%20army%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTake%20a%20census%20of%20all%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%26%23x2014%3Bfrom%20Beersheba%20in%20the%20south%20to%20Dan%20in%20the%20north%26%23x2014%3Band%20bring%20me%20a%20report%20so%20I%20may%20know%20how%20many%20there%20are.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_21_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Joab%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMay%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20his%20people%20a%20hundred%20times%20over!%20But%20why%2C%20my%20lord%20the%20king%2C%20do%20you%20want%20to%20do%20this%3F%20Are%20they%20not%20all%20your%20servants%3F%20Why%20must%20you%20cause%20Israel%20to%20sin%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_21_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20king%20insisted%20that%20they%20take%20the%20census%2C%20so%20Joab%20traveled%20throughout%20all%20Israel%20to%20count%20the%20people.%20Then%20he%20returned%20to%20Jerusalem%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_21_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20reported%20the%20number%20of%20people%20to%20David.%20There%20were%201%2C100%2C000%20warriors%20in%20all%20Israel%20who%20could%20handle%20a%20sword%2C%20and%20470%2C000%20in%20Judah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_21_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Joab%20did%20not%20include%20the%20tribes%20of%20Levi%20and%20Benjamin%20in%20the%20census%20because%20he%20was%20so%20distressed%20at%20what%20the%20king%20had%20made%20him%20do.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_21_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJudgment%20for%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Sin%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EGod%20was%20very%20displeased%20with%20the%20census%2C%20and%20he%20punished%20Israel%20for%20it.%20%3Cvers